id: pm-lwbr
title: Accept pm init --yes alias for --defaults
description: Many agent harnesses default to typing `--yes`/`-y` for non-interactive bootstrap. `pm init --yes` errors with 'Unknown option --yes'. Add `--yes` (and `-y`) as alias for `--defaults` in register-setup.ts and document it in help. Keeps token efficiency and reduces friction during first-time agent setup.
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,cli,init,pm-cli
created_at: "2026-05-17T19:19:24.505Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-17T19:45:28.921Z"
author: claude-code-agent
acceptance_criteria: pm init --yes works equivalent to --defaults; pm init -y works; help shows alias; regression test added
parent: pm-rnpb
resolution: Added -y/--yes as an alias for pm init --defaults and surfaced it through contracts and completions.
expected_result: "pm init --yes and pm init -y run non-interactive defaults like --defaults, and agents can discover the alias without retrying."
actual_result: "Integration, contracts, completion, dogfood, and release gates passed with the alias available."
